roles/build-containers/templates/build.s.message:
this is a total style nit, but I would like to see us format the jinja like so

    openstack tripleo container image build \
    {%   if push_containers|bool %}
        --push \
    {%   endif %}
        --base ubi8 \
    {%   if distro is defined %}
        --distro {{ distro }} \
    {%   endif %}
    {%   if excludes is defined %}
        {{ excludes }} \
    {%   endif %}
        --config-file {{ openstack_git_root }}/tripleo-common/container-images/tripleo_containers.yaml \
        --config-path {{ openstack_git_root }}/tripleo-common/container-images \
        --work-dir /tmp/container-builds \
        --debug 2> containers-build-errors.log
    {% endif %}

When we format the commands like so it provides a nice way to read the template but also gets rid of extra newlines and whitespace around the rendered commands.

